= Links

Link objects create hyperlinks to external URLs and internal references.

== Basic Link

{{link:https://example.com}}

== Link with Text

{{link:https://example.com text="Example Website"}}

{{link:https://github.com text="GitHub"}}

== Link with Target

{{link:https://example.com text="Example" target=_blank}}

== Link with Hreflang

{{link:https://example.com text="Example" hreflang=en}}

== Link Examples

{{link:https://example.com text="Homepage"}}

{{link:https://docs.example.com text="Documentation"}}

{{link:https://github.com/example text="GitHub Repository"}}

== Link in Paragraphs

This paragraph contains a link: {{link:https://example.com text="click here"}}.

== Multiple Links

Visit {{link:https://example.com text="Example"}} and {{link:https://github.com text="GitHub"}}.

== Link with Attributes

{{link:https://example.com text="Example Website" target=_blank hreflang=en}}

== Link Object Syntax

The link object uses the format: `{{link:url text="Link Text" target=_blank}}`

Where:
* `url` - The URL or key for the link
* `text` - Optional link text (defaults to titleized version of the key)
* `target` - Optional target attribute (e.g., _blank)
* `hreflang` - Optional language attribute
